    "section_custom_code_7m4C4T": {
      "type": "section-custom-code",
      "name": "Custom code",
      "settings": {
        "code": "<!-- Wrapper container using unique selectors to avoid CSS conflicts -->\n<div class=\"rb-layout-container\">\n    \n    <!-- Left-aligned text section taking up the remaining space (approx 70%) -->\n    <div class=\"rb-layout-text-section\">\n        <h1 class=\"rb-layout-title\">Celebrating Three Decades of Iconic Style and Craftsmanship</h1>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">Ravi Bajaj has remained a defining force in Indian fashion for over 37 years, known for his precision tailoring, innovation, and commitment to slow fashion.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">His journey in the industry began at just 16, when Indian fashion had limited room for experimentation. While others adhered to traditional designs, Bajaj embraced a bold, avant-garde approach, introducing unconventional fabrics, striking color palettes, and impeccable craftsmanship. Initially met with skepticism, his vision later earned widespread recognition, cementing his status as one of India's most respected designers.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">On December 13, 1987, he launched his first store, a space that defied conventional design norms. Envisioning a monochrome aesthetic long before it became mainstream, he sought black-and-white interiors but when black granite proved impractical, he used white temple stone rubbed with kohl to achieve the desired effect. This resourcefulness became a hallmark of his career, demonstrating his ability to turn challenges into creative solutions.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">His collections from the very beginning included both menswear and womenswear—an unusual approach at the time. Initially introducing Western silhouettes inspired by his time in London, he later adapted to India's evolving fashion landscape by expanding into ethnic wear, developing a signature black-and-white saree line that became synonymous with his brand.</p>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">Beyond fashion, Bajaj has worked on high-profile corporate projects, designing uniforms for some of the country's most prestigious brands. His first major corporate assignment came in 1987 when he designed uniforms for Pavilion Restaurant. This led to a long-standing collaboration with Hyatt, where he became a global panel member, influencing the luxury hospitality industry's sartorial choices. His expertise was further sought by Jet Airways, where he designed uniforms for 6,000 employees across departments. Despite never actively pursuing celebrity endorsements, his designs caught the attention of Amitabh Bachchan, who personally selected Bajaj to dress him for an entire season of Kaun Banega Crorepati (Season 4).</p>\n\n        <p class=\"rb-layout-paragraph\">His commitment to slow fashion remains central to his brand ethos. Rejecting the fast-paced trends of the industry, he focuses on creating heirloom-worthy pieces that stand the test of time. His designs are crafted with meticulous attention to detail, emphasizing longevity and quality. Over three decades later, he continues to push boundaries, blending heritage with modernity while maintaining his dedication to craftsmanship. His legacy is not just about fashion, it's about redefining luxury, setting new standards and proving that true style is timeless.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Right-aligned image section taking up exactly 30% width -->\n    <div class=\"rb-layout-image-section\">\n        <!-- Replace src with your actual image path -->\n        <img class=\"rb-layout-img\" src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0764/8932/6755/files/AboutImageRavi_jpg.jpg?v=1784295401\" alt=\"Ravi Bajaj Feature Image\">\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n<style>\n    /* Encapsulated Layout CSS - isolated using custom 'rb-layout-' prefix */\n    .rb-layout-container {\n        display: flex;\n        width: 100%;\n        max-width: 1200px;\n        margin: 0 auto;\n        gap: 40px;\n        align-items: flex-start;\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n    }\n\n    .rb-layout-container *, \n    .rb-layout-container *::before, \n    .rb-layout-container *::after {\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n    }\n\n    /* Left-aligned text configuration */\n    .rb-layout-text-section {\n        width: 70%;\n        text-align: left; /* Left alignment */\n    }\n\n    .rb-layout-title {\n        font-family: 'Georgia', serif;\n        font-size: 1.85rem;\n        font-weight: bold;\n        line-height: 1.3;\n        margin: 0 0 24px 0;\n        color: #000;\n    }\n\n    .rb-layout-paragraph {\n        font-family: 'Georgia', serif;\n        font-size: 1.05rem;\n        line-height: 1.6;\n        margin: 0 0 24px 0;\n        color: #222;\n    }\n\n    /* 30% Width Image Section on the Right */\n    .rb-layout-image-section {\n        width: 30%;\n        position: -webkit-sticky;\n        position: sticky;\n            top: 150px;\n    }\n\n    .rb-layout-img {\n        display: block;\n        width: 100%;\n        height: auto;\n        object-fit: cover;\n        border-radius: 4px;\n    }\n\n    /* Mobile Responsive adjustments */\n    @media (max-width: 768px) {\n        .rb-layout-container {\n            flex-direction: column-reverse; /* Places image on top for mobile screens */\n            gap: 24px;\n        }\n        .rb-layout-text-section,\n        .rb-layout-image-section {\n            width: 100%;\n            position: static;\n        }\n    }\n</style>",
        "width": "wrapper",
